==English==

===Etymology===
[[Euphemism]] for ''[[god]]''.

===Interjection===
'''gosh!'''

# A mild expression of surprise or enthusiasm as to be put in place of "god".
#: ''Gosh, I didn't realize I'd cause so much trouble!''
#: ''Gosh I'd love to go to that concert!''

